text: Over three acres of property in a great location! This property has a building permit in process. Well is in, septic is in, and the permitting process is nearly complete. Property has a nice pond on it; depending on your new home's location, you could have a view of the pond. This property is only one of two properties on this private road and it is surrounded by fields which gives you a private setting. There is an old single wide on the property. No restrictions on this property and no HOA. Manufactured homes OK.

This charming home features a huge shop, new roof, & recently stained deck, perfect for enjoying breathtaking sunsets over the seasonal pond. The spacious back deck invites you to unwind while soaking in the natural beauty of your surroundings. Inside, youre greeted w/tasteful finishes throughout the home, along w/cozy fireplaces. The property has a natural spring well water system, providing water year-round. The expansive shop offers ample space & is ready for your hobbies & projects. It also is equipped w/a hardwired air compressor & is ready for you to add a wood stove to stay warm on those chilly days working in the shop. Dont miss out on this unique opportunity to own a home that combines functionality w/stunning natural beauty.

Enjoy luxurious living in desirable Bow with this majestic home on 2+ acres. No detail has been missed with extensive high-end updates. This custom home was designed with vaulted ceilings & huge windows to take in westerly views of the bay & spectacular sunsets. The main floor primary suite is like no other, with private access to the deck, sauna, steam shower, soaker tub, double vanities, and closetsall finished in marble. The airy kitchen is open to a sunroom and outdoor deck. Downstairs, find a family room/gym, safe room, new laundry, & 2 large bedrooms/bathsall in marble. In addition, a 3-car garage with cabinets & workbench. The peaceful, professionally landscaped property has an orchard, fenced garden, & community tennis courts!

This beautifully updated home offers an inviting open-concept layout with laminate flooring throughout the living, dining, and kitchen areas. Abundant natural light pours in through a picture window and skylight. The remodeled kitchen features white shaker cabinets and stainless steel appliances. Bedrooms boast newer carpet, and the home is enhanced with chair rail accents and fully trimmed windows and doors. Enjoy the fully fenced backyard with a spacious deck, perfect for entertaining. Conveniently located near town, state parks, and the Anacortes trailhead.

Welcome to this beautiful three-bedroom home in the Skagit Highlands! The inviting main floor layout features a cozy living room with a fireplace, a well-equipped kitchen with ample storage and a spacious island, a dining room, a convenient laundry room, and a half bath. Upstairs, you'll find a large primary suite with a luxurious 5-piece ensuite bath and an expansive walk-in closet. A good-sized loft, two additional bedrooms, and a full bath complete the upper level. The amazing fully fenced outdoor space is perfect for entertaining, boasting a covered patio, hot tub, and dog run. Enjoy easy access to I-5 and WA-9, as well as nearby parks and trails. Dont miss the opportunity to make this wonderful home yours!

Discover the ideal location for your camper, RV, or manufactured home in the charming Cape Horn community. This flexible lot is perfect for year-round living or as a weekend retreat. With water and electricity already on-site, setting up is effortless. Enjoy quick access to the beautiful Skagit River, a haven for fishing enthusiasts and nature lovers alike. The community park adds to the appeal with amenities like a playground, a gazebo with picnic tables, and a basketball court, making it an ideal spot for gatherings and leisurely activities. Take advantage of the many nearby trails to fully experience the natural splendor of the Pacific Northwest. Build your dream home and embrace all that this enchanting location has to offer!

Brand New Community Bay View in the Burlington Country Club Area. Home will be complete Sept 10th. The plan features 1888 sq ft with 4 bedrooms, 2.5 baths. Island Kitchen opens to Great Room, dining area. Primary Bedroom with Large 5 piece Bath, stand alone tub, walk-in shower and walk-in closet. 3 additional Bedrooms up. Large back patio and covered front porch. Bay View schools. Next to Skagit Golf and Country Club, Edison, Chuckanut, La Conner and Anacortes. Shopping and I-5 minutes away. Special Financing options when working with the Preferred Lender. Buyers are able to customize finishes at the Design Center. For GPS use 16850 Peterson Road.

Come and see this lovely 3 bedroom and 2 bathroom 1994 double-wide manufactured home on a full acre of flat, mostly open, usable land. There is plenty of room to be private, enjoy seclusion, yet close enough to be in town in about 20 minutes. There is a single car garage with a shop built in as well. Plenty of room for hobby work. With this home nearly at the end of a dead end street, you won't suffer the sound of cars rushing by. This home and land are quiet, spacious, and peaceful. Definitely a place you can unwind from the stresses of everyday life. There are mature trees as well as many bushes, grass, and shrubs. The home is features a kitchen, living room, and dining room that all make up on big great room feel. Don't miss out!

{Turn Key 3 Bed/2 Bath Home w/Large Lot & Fenced Backyard!}This home has it all. Enter through the covered porch entrance into an open concept living area that flows into the kitchen. Both kitchen & living area have lots of natural lighting. Enjoy the breakfast nook or step out your sliding glass door into the huge backyard that is level & fully fenced. Backyard provides ample space for entertaining, gardening or just relaxation. Nice sized primary w/primary bath. Ideally located near shopping, restaurants, medical, interstate & much more. Fresh paint throughout the inside w/nice stainless appliances that all stay! This home is in great condition & ready for its' next owner. Come see it before it's gone.

Experience tranquility and privacy in the LIKE NEW Single Level Home surrounded by acres of protected greenbelt. Builders last and favorite lot. Step out your front door to a beautiful, treed trail for long walks. This lightly lived in home sits on a large corner lot, next to the serene park. Home boasts quarts countertops, HUGE center Island for entertaining, High-end appliances, vaulted ceilings, walk-in-closets and pantry. lovely utility room. Enjoy the primary suite with spa bath vessel tub all overlooking your fully fenced backyard and greenbelt. 3 Bed PLUS den with barn door. This home soars with natural light and is energy efficient. Highly sought after newer neighborhood. Close to all amenities, parks and trails. A home to brag about.

Beautifully remodeled in 2016, this 1, 195 sq. ft home features 3 bedrooms, 1.75 bath, blending modern upgrades with timeless charm for cozy living. Freshly painted interior and exterior. Step into the open concept living room and spacious kitchen with eating bar, updated appliances and granite countertops. New electrical, plumbing, insulation, water heater and roof were installed at the time of remodel. New sewer line was replaced in 2022. Spacious two-car garage/shop with built-in storage shelves, plus an additional parking space. Move in ready and waiting for your personal touch. Just minutes away from schools, shopping, dining and local amenities.

Located in beautiful Shelter Bay, this home is a must see! Fresh exterior paint (July 2024) and new roof and gutters in 2017. Well cared for with a finished basement and beautiful deck means plenty of space to spread out. Come see all the things Shelter Bay and La Conner have to offer. This home is on leased land.

Get ready to fall in love with this sweet home with great curb appeal in the peaceful Mt. Vernon Heights neighborhood. 1153 sq/ft featuring beautiful built-in shelving and a stunning fireplace with new wood stove insert. Attractive laminate flooring shines in living areas with warm carpet in the bedrooms. Completely remodeled in 2016 and more recently a new tub making the bathroom feel shiny and new! The delightful backyard includes a lovely shade tree, berry bushes, roses and even a unique outdoor fireplace! There is a charming trellis/sitting area, nice shed and gorgeous spot for a garden or chickens if you desire. Fully fenced too! Minutes to downtown Mt. Vernon and to I5. This home has it all- come see it in person today!

This charming home, conveniently located near town and ferries, offers a blend of comfort and style. The beautifully updated kitchen features elegant white cabinetry, a sleek tile backsplash, and durable quartz countertops, perfect for culinary adventures. A large mudroom area provides practicality, while the primary bedroom boasts vaulted ceilings and a private balcony for serene relaxation. Upstairs, a spacious bonus room offers versatile use. The fenced backyard, complete with terraced decks and built-in garden space, invites outdoor enjoyment. Located across from the baseball fields and Kiwanis Meadows, with the Anacortes trailhead just up the road, this home is ideally situated for active living.

Brand New Community Bay View under construction in the Burlington Country Club Area. The plan features 1888 sq ft with 4 bedrooms, 2.5 baths. Kitchen Island opens to Great Room, dining area. Primary Bedroom with Large 5 piece Bath and walk-in closet upstairs with 3 other Bedrooms. Large back patio and covered front porch. Bay View schools. Close to Skagit Country Club, Edison, Chuckanut, La Conner and Anacortes. Shopping a short distance away. Home to be complete mid September. Special Financing options when working with the Preferred Lender. Buyers are able to customize finishes at the Design Center. For GPS: 16850 Peterson Road.

Built in 2006 & meticulously loved & maintained, this home is move-in ready! W/20+ ft ceilings, wainscoting, much of the living is done on the main floor including the primary bedroom, complete w/full bath, two sinks & walk-in closet. Also on the main-the den/office, living, dining, utility & kitchen, which boasts granite countertops, newer appliances, Kohler cast iron sink, under cabinet lighting, pantry & bar seating, great for entertaining. The den/office is off tiled entryway, The slider on the main opens to covered deck & fully fenced backyard. Down the steps you'll find entertaining space for evenings spent outside, along w/a shed. Storage is immense & the three-car tandem garage could also be utilized as storage/shop/workout area.

Step back in time to Grandma's house in this lovingly maintained, vintage mid-century home situated in peaceful setting walkable to the park, baseball & soccer fields, playground & Community Forest Land Trails. This treasured gem has been enjoyed by several generations. If the walls could only talk! It offers a convenient kitchen, cozy family room, living room, warm dining space for hosting holiday dinners. 1020 SF detached garage/shop space with power. Fenced yard, fruit tree and lots of mature plantings in the garden all on shy 15, 000 SF lot. Newer roof, leaf guards for gutters. New 200 amp electrical panel. Structural supports in the crawl space being addressed by contractor will be complete prior to closing. So many possibilities!

Incredible updated home with main level living on 8.49 acres plus a massive shop for all your hobbies. This 2, 002 sqft home has been meticulously maintained & updated. Main level with gorgeous kitchen including Quartz countertops, custom cabinetry, large island & tile floors. Living room with gorgeous hardwood floors, a pellet stove to keep you cozy in the winter plus a mini-split heat pump for heating & A/C. Spacious primary bedroom on main level with 2 closets, walk in shower & two vanities. Upstairs with two large rooms plus full bathroom. Landing area for office/playroom. 2 car detached garage plus a 4, 200 sq ft shop with metal roof, 6 standard doors plus a 13' RV door. Level acreage & access to Nookachamps Creek. Extensive landscaping.

Impeccably maintained and ready for you to move right in, this home boasts beautiful landscaping & hardscaping, complete with privacy shrubs & a fully fenced yard for peace of mind. Inside, the vaulted ceiling living room welcomes you with a cozy gas fireplace, while the spacious kitchen features walnut-colored cabinetry, a built-in buffet, & ample eat-in space. Bedrooms are generously sized, & the updated bathrooms add a touch of modern comfort. Bonus features include a newer roof, updated appliances, & a convenient garden shed with extended covered ports, complemented by a charming paver patio. This home is a perfect blend of comfort, convenience, and style. Home is located outside of the 100-year flood zone. No flood insurance required.

Discover your dream home in the quiet gated community of Creekside Village. This low-maintenance 3-bedroom rambler is nestled on a private lot, offering serene views of the creek & woods. The inviting covered front porch leads to a great room w/vaulted ceilings, gas fp, oversized windows & dining space. Enjoy cooking in the spacious kitchen w/double oven, ample storage space & breakfast nook. Retreat to the primary bedrm w/en-suite bath & walk-in closet. Relax on the private deck. With a 2-car garage & all appliances included, this home is move-in ready. HOA covers exterior maintenance, yard care & road upkeep. The complex also offers RV parking possibilities. Conveniently located near Fidalgo pool, senior center, schools & all amenities.

Discover the opportunity to own a breathtaking parcel of land adjacent to 16546 Highway 9 in serene Mount Vernon, WA. This expansive lot offers stunning territorial and Mount Baker views, perfect for creating your rural retreat or investment property. Zoning: Rural Reserve zoning ensures low-density development, preserving the open space and rural character of the area. This zoning is ideal for those looking for moderate acreage, residential, or limited employment opportunities. The property includes wetlands. No current wetland studies are available, and the wetlands have not been delineated or mitigated. Whether you're looking to build a dream home or invest in a piece of rural paradise, this property offers endless possibilities.

Explore a unique opportunity at this expansive property featuring FOUR shipping containers for ample storage, an outdoor shop, and a cozy shack ideal for parking a small trailer. The property is secured with a basic entry gate, ensuring privacy and convenience. The main living building is a mobile home, which is in livable condition, providing a comfortable space while you envision the potential of the land. Although the property contains some clutter as we are in the process of selling items, it offers a blank canvas for your creativity. Whether you seek a personal retreat, a storage solution, or a project to transform, this property has the potential to meet your needs. Dont miss out on this versatile space!

Beautiful 2448 SQFT spacious home with 4 bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms in a quiet sought after neighborhood of Forest Hills. This home is only a minutes drive to downtown Anacortes. Close proximity to popular Anacortes Community Forest Land trails. This is a must see home and an amazing opportunity to not miss out on!

Welcome to your new oasis in this highly sought-after 55+ neighborhood! This beautifully maintained 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom home offers the perfect blend of comfort and style in a vibrant community designed for active adults. The well-equipped kitchen features contemporary appliances and ample storage. Your private primary bedroom boasts a spacious layout, a walk-in closet, and an en-suite bathroom. The large living room looks out over your private front porch. The home features a 2 car garage and storage galore. Enjoy time getting to know your neighbors at The Cedars Clubhouse. RV parking available through community. All of this and only minutes for shopping, parks, I-5 and hospitals. Make this your Next Home.

First time on the Market! Come check out this wonderful well kept Skagit Golf and Country Club mid century modern home. Great location close to golf course clubhouse and just minutes to town. This mid century classic has lots of light and open space to enjoy the views with vaulted ceilings and open staircase. 3 nice sized bedrooms upstairs with walk in closet and bath off the primary bedroom. Great home for entertaining with large cooks kitchen and eating area that opens to spacious family room. Large dining room opens up to beautiful living room with cozy fireplace. Lovely back patio with beautiful landscaping for outdoor gatherings. Large lot with space to park an RV and lots of parking on big circular driveway. Don't miss this one!

Great bones in this 4 bedroom, home located in a nice neighborhood with partial views of the Guemes Channel and San Juan Islands. Large fenced South facing back yard perfect for gardening.Plenty of parking for an RV. The home is in need of maintenance, repairs and updates to make it shine! Looking for a fixer upper? Look no further. Bring your imagination and build some sweat equity. Selling as is.

Experience the charm of this bright condo with stunning marina views in Shelter Bay! Enjoy the spacious living room with a woodburning stove and a large picture window showcasing breathtaking views. The kitchen, equipped with stainless steel appliances and ample counter space, opens to a dining room with bamboo floors and a built-in buffet. Upstairs, the primary bedroom boasts vaulted ceilings and an office with extra windows, a second bedroom, a bath, and a laundry closet. Relax or entertain on the expansive back deck, perfect for lounging and outdoor dining. Enjoy easy access to a Par 3 nine-hole golf course, beach access, playgrounds, sports courts, and a clubhouse. Conveniently located near downtown La Conner and Hwy 20!

Nestled in the popular Skagit Highlands, this spacious and versatile two-story home offers a charming front porch entry leading to an open floor plan. The generous kitchen area boasts ample storage cabinetry and a center island with seating, seamlessly flowing to the outdoor patio, pergola, and backyard framed by boulders. The primary suite features a walk-in closet and a spacious bathroom with a soaking tub, tile and glass shower, and dual sinks. Three additional bedrooms and a generous landing area offer potential for a workspace, play zone, or media area. The property includes an attached 2-car garage and driveway parking. Enjoy Skagit Creek Park across the street, with mountain views and nearby trails. This home awaits your presence!

Fantastic Mount Vernon rambler located on a quiet cul de sac in one of the area's best neighborhoods! This 3 bedroom 2 bath house built in 2010 is in excellent condition. You'll appreciate the flowing 1-level floor plan on a daily basis! Big kitchen flooded with natural light, upgraded appliances, granite counters, tile floors & ample storage adjacent to the dining room. Wonderful hardwood floors and gas fireplace. Main ensuite offers 5-piece bath & large walk-in closet. The west-facing rear of the home offers generous deck that overlooks a low-maintenance landscaped yard with well-thought-out flora, pond, abundant fruit trees & abuts a city wetland buffer & terrific finished hobby building insulated with power. RV/Boat Parking, No HOA!

[PEACEFUL SETTING] BRICKYARD PARK a new 55+ Community! This lightly lived in 3 bed 1.75 bath RAMBLER has all the upgrades. Entertainers Dream home w/all living spaces feeling connected + vaulted ceilings. Wood laminate floors, GAS FIREPLACE, Upgraded Cabinetry, QUARTZ countertops, stainless appliances + lighting. Wide hallways, 3 generous size bedrooms & window treatments. Primary bed w/stunning private bath w/plenty of counter space. Gas forced air heat + HEAT PUMP for A/C. Gardeners dream w/beautiful mature plants, covered front/back porches for outdoor living. 2 car garage & plenty of parking. Landscaping of front & backyards included in HOA. Clubhouse, walking trails, park, pickleball + stage for outdoor events. [FOREVER HOME]

Beautiful home with two parcels that could be combined and subdivided into a buildable lot (or possibly two!). Open plan home with airy, light-filled living room featuring skylights and plenty of windows plus gas stove. Bright, spacious kitchen also enjoys natural light from the skylights and windows plus gorgeous hardwood floors. Laundry/mud room with tile flooring. Charming, partially covered deck overlooks the lovely mature landscaping, garden space, fruit trees, as well as both lake and mountain views outside of bloom season. Huge barn plus outbuildings for tons of covered storage space for your vehicles & toys. Keep the entire acreage to yourself or enjoy the income potential of creating and selling off a buildable lot or possibly two.

Enjoy privacy and seclusion with stunning views of the sunrise over Mt. Baker, the historic La Conner, Rainbow Bridge, Marina, channel Waterway, the tulip fields surrounded by eagles and blue herons. You can entertain in the open great room with a kitchen overlooking the view or on the wrap-around deck. There's also an attached but separate bonus room that could serve as a 3rd bedroom, hobby room, or den/office. The private owner suite offers additional comfort. You can take advantage of Shelter Bay amenities, including a swimming pool, tennis courts, clubhouse, private beach, golf course, and a concrete boat ramp for your trips into the quaint little town of La Conner. Natural landscaping.

Surround yourself with nature as a part of the beautiful Shelter Bay coastal community. This property offers year-round vacation living with breathtaking views and community amenities such as swimming, golf, tennis, and a private beach. Inside, beautiful vaulted wood ceilings and large windows capture panoramic views of the Northern Cascade mountains. Ample space allows for easy living and entertaining. A large wrap-around deck offers marina and snow capped mountain views, ideal for relaxing or dining outdoors. Additional features include a large fireplace, private hot tub, low-maintenance landscaping and plenty of off-street parking.This home offers comfort and convenience for a peaceful but active lifestyle of the Pacific Northwest.

Motivated Seller! Escape to the tranquility of mountain living in this charming 5-bedroom, 3-bathroom home, perfectly situated to offer breathtaking views and serene surroundings. This home is a true retreat, offering the ideal blend of rustic charm & modern amenities, making it perfect for nature lovers and anyone seeking a peaceful escape. Step inside to a welcoming living room adorned w/ vaulted ceilings, ample natural light, & a beautiful stone fireplace that's perfect for cozying up on cool mountain evenings. A second living space for additional income (MIL)! Relax on the giant deck that wraps around the home, perfect for outdoor dining, entertaining, or simply soaking in the stunning mountain views.

Impeccably restored bungalow is a fusion of historic allure & contemporary sophistication. From the moment you step foot onto this 1 acre pastoral paradise, you will be amazed by a standard of living that invites you to indulge in the serene beauty that surrounds you. Inside, the meticulously renovated interiors seamlessly blend old-world charm with modern comforts, creating a home that resonates warmth & elegance. The 2019 remodel spared no expense, revealing a kitchen adorned with top-of-the-line appliances, quartz countertops, complemented by classic yet refined details throughout. Charming bonus room on main floor doubles as a convenient office/guest room. Create your dream lifestyle by expanding the gardens, adding a shop, barn or ADU!

Welcome to the enchanting world of the Lake Cavenaugh community. Just 30 minutes east from Highway 9 in Mount Vernon. Lake Cavanaugh is very sought after real estate. Three separate sleeping quarters, sleep 2 people's each. Small kitchen with a view in main cabin. Lake water snubbed to both bldgs. 63 feet of waterfront on the Southshore boasting a 90 foot dock, a boat house with launch pulley. There are three quaint cabin's including the boathouse with a deck on top for sunbathing and enjoying the views of the islands, mountains, northern and easterly views. There are no HOA's or CCR's. This sale includes two lots (the front lot on the water and the back lot). A big viewing deck on the boathouse. Summer is here, come have a look!

Beautifully updated home, in prime location w/ park in front and great neighborhood walking trails. Main floor has an open concept floor plan w/ dual-sided fireplace separating the living and dining area. The main also has an office w/ double pocket doors, a 1/2 bath and kitchen w/ SS appliances, an island w/ bar seating and an immense pantry. The kitchen opens to a fully fenced backyard patio which backs onto the greenbelt and walking trails. The Primary bedroom upstairs overlooks the park, has plenty of space, a large walk-in closet, and 2 bathroom vanities. The large open lounge area at the top of the stairs separates the primary suite from 2 other bedrooms, a 2nd bathroom and laundry. Everything is ready to begin enjoying life!

High-end Craftsman home in gated community w/ spectacular architectural features and high-pitched roof! Enjoy the rich details of this quality-build featuring luxury vinyl plank flooring, 9 foot ceilings, custom plastered fireplace, contemporary black windows, waterfall kitchen island w/ matte black sink, and solid quartz counters throughout. Luxurious heated tile floors, Jack & Jill vanities, freestanding soaking tub, walk-in tile shower with frameless glass shower door. Electric high efficiency water heater, and ductless heat pump and A/C, pressurized septic system. Stick-built 28'x36' garage/shop with 14' tall ceilings, space for storage/workbench, RV doors, 200 Amp power, frost-free water hydrant and smooth finish concrete slab.
